---
import IdeasSidebar from "../../components/IdeasSidebar.astro";
---

<html lang="en" data-theme="dark">
  <head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8" />
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0" />
    <title>mosarch: Architecture as a live, semantic graph</title>
    <meta
      name="description"
      content="mosarch models systems from business capabilities through components, interfaces, and protocols as typed concepts in a depict knowledge graph. Every stakeholder gets a different view of the same architecture. Every view is a query, not a separate document."
    />
    <link rel="icon" type="image/x-icon" href="/favicon.ico" />
    <link rel="icon" type="image/png" sizes="32x32" href="/images/favicon-32x32.png" />
    <link rel="icon" type="image/png" sizes="16x16" href="/images/favicon-16x16.png" />
    <link rel="apple-touch-icon" sizes="180x180" href="/images/apple-touch-icon.png" />
    <link rel="stylesheet" href="https://fonts.googleapis.com/css2?family=Inter:wght@400;500;600;700;800&family=JetBrains+Mono:wght@400;500;600&display=swap" />
    <link rel="stylesheet" href="/assets/css/landing.css" />
    <link rel="stylesheet" href="/assets/css/hub-subproject.css" />
  </head>
  <body class="hub-subproject">
    <IdeasSidebar active="mosarch" />

    <div class="hub-main">
      <section class="hero">
        <div class="hub-status-row">
          <span class="hub-chip draft">🧊 Draft: concept only</span>
          <span class="hub-chip">depict domain ontology</span>
          <span class="hub-chip">TOGAF · C4 · ArchiMate · ADRs</span>
          <span class="hub-chip">Multi-stakeholder views</span>
        </div>
        <h1>One model. Many views. <span class="accent">Diagrams that derive themselves.</span></h1>
        <p class="tagline">mosarch models systems from business capabilities through components, interfaces, and protocols as typed concepts in a depict knowledge graph. Every stakeholder gets a different view of the same architecture. Every view is a query, not a separate document.</p>
      </section>

      <section class="section">
        <div class="intent-callout">
          <h3>Intent</h3>
          <p>Architecture lives in 12 different disconnected tools: Visio, Confluence, git repos, terraform, kubernetes, openapi, jira, notion, lucidchart, miro, gsheet, email. Everyone knows they disagree. Nobody wins. mosarch's bet: <strong>architecture is a single knowledge graph, views are queries over that graph, and diagrams are derived from views.</strong> Ingest facts from running systems. Model decisions as first-class nodes. Every stakeholder asks the same graph for their view. The whole system has provenance.</p>
        </div>
      </section>

      <section class="section">
        <div class="section-label">The idea in one picture</div>
        <h2>Ingest, extract, align, query, render</h2>
        <p class="section-desc">Every input is a live fact source. Every output is a derived view. The middle is depict: aligned facts with provenance.</p>
        <div class="pipe-diagram">ingest.docs ──┐
ingest.repos ─┤
ingest.k8s ───┼──→ extract.arch.facts ──→ align.arch.ontology ──→ depict.store.graph ──┐
ingest.iac ───┤                                                                        │
ingest.openapi┘                                                                       ├──→ view.derive(stakeholder) ──→ per-role UI
                                                                                      ├──→ options.analyze(decision) ──→ tradeoff matrix
                                                                                      └──→ diagram.render(view) ──→ SVG+interactive</div>
      </section>

      <section class="section">
        <div class="section-label">Design principles</div>
        <h2>Six things mosarch holds firm</h2>
        <div class="diff-grid">
          <div class="diff-card">
            <div class="diff-icon primary">📐</div>
            <h3>Architecture is a graph not a diagram</h3>
            <p>Systems are nodes. Relationships are edges. Every concept is typed (capability, component, service, endpoint, protocol, decision). The graph is the source of truth. Diagrams are rendered views.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="diff-card">
            <div class="diff-icon accent">👥</div>
            <h3>Views are queries not documents</h3>
            <p>Developer sees different architecture than network admin, security, infra, compliance. Each is a pre-built query against the same graph. No separate docs. No drift. Every view is generated, current, role-specific.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="diff-card">
            <div class="diff-icon success">⚖️</div>
            <h3>Decisions are first-class nodes</h3>
            <p>ADRs live in the graph as Decision nodes. Options and tradeoffs are edges. Analysis queries span the decision space. You ask the graph "what are the security tradeoffs for this component?" not a spreadsheet.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="diff-card">
            <div class="diff-icon light">🔄</div>
            <h3>Ingests from running systems</h3>
            <p>Kubernetes clusters are live sources. Terraform plans are ingested. OpenAPI specs define interfaces. Dockerfile inspections extract layer facts. Architecture drifts. Detection is a query, not a manual review.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="diff-card">
            <div class="diff-icon error">📊</div>
            <h3>Diagrams are derived projections</h3>
            <p>SVG, interactive, Mermaid: all rendered on-demand from the same graph. Change the architecture in depict, all diagrams auto-update. Render for a specific stakeholder role, a specific timeframe, a specific decision scope.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="diff-card">
            <div class="diff-icon muted">🔗</div>
            <h3>Built on depict</h3>
            <p>Every node and edge carries provenance: source document, ingest step, alignment decision, timestamp. Architecture drift is traceable. You know which component came from k8s vs. terraform vs. hand-authored markdown.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </section>

      <section class="section">
        <div class="section-label">Step library (target)</div>
        <h2>Ingest, extract, align, view, decide, render</h2>
        <div class="pkg-grid">
          <div class="pkg-card"><div class="pkg-name">ingest.markdown.adr</div><div class="pkg-desc">ADR markdown files → Decision nodes</div></div>
          <div class="pkg-card"><div class="pkg-name">ingest.openapi.spec</div><div class="pkg-desc">OpenAPI / Swagger → Interface nodes</div></div>
          <div class="pkg-card"><div class="pkg-name">ingest.kubernetes.cluster</div><div class="pkg-desc">Live k8s cluster → Service + Pod nodes</div></div>
          <div class="pkg-card"><div class="pkg-name">ingest.terraform.plan</div><div class="pkg-desc">Terraform state → Infrastructure nodes</div></div>
          <div class="pkg-card"><div class="pkg-name">ingest.dockerfile</div><div class="pkg-desc">Dockerfile inspection → Build layer facts</div></div>
          <div class="pkg-card"><div class="pkg-name">extract.arch.facts</div><div class="pkg-desc">Entity + relation extraction from sources</div></div>
          <div class="pkg-card"><div class="pkg-name">align.arch.ontology</div><div class="pkg-desc">Align facts to TOGAF/C4/ArchiMate types</div></div>
          <div class="pkg-card"><div class="pkg-name">view.derive</div><div class="pkg-desc">Generate role-specific view queries</div></div>
          <div class="pkg-card"><div class="pkg-name">view.render.svg</div><div class="pkg-desc">Render view as SVG diagram</div></div>
          <div class="pkg-card"><div class="pkg-name">view.render.interactive</div><div class="pkg-desc">Interactive graph viewer with drill-down</div></div>
          <div class="pkg-card"><div class="pkg-name">options.analyze</div><div class="pkg-desc">Compute tradeoffs for a decision</div></div>
          <div class="pkg-card"><div class="pkg-name">adr.capture</div><div class="pkg-desc">Structured ADR capture form</div></div>
          <div class="pkg-card"><div class="pkg-name">adr.link.outcome</div><div class="pkg-desc">Link decision outcome to architecture fact</div></div>
          <div class="pkg-card"><div class="pkg-name">drift.detect.cluster</div><div class="pkg-desc">Diff running cluster against modeled arch</div></div>
        </div>
      </section>

      <section class="section section-centered">
        <div class="section-label">The architecture</div>
        <h2>Four layers, one model</h2>
        <div class="arch-visual">
          <div class="arch-layer accent">
            Diagrams+Views <span class="desc">SVG · Interactive · Mermaid · Per-role UI</span>
          </div>
          <div class="arch-arrow">render &#8595;</div>
          <div class="arch-layer light">
            mosarch <span class="desc">TOGAF · C4 · ArchiMate · ADRs · Decisions</span>
          </div>
          <div class="arch-arrow">query &#8595;</div>
          <div class="arch-layer success">
            depict <span class="desc">Core types · alignment · provenance · GraphQL · federation</span>
          </div>
          <div class="arch-arrow">built on &#8595;</div>
          <div class="arch-layer deep">
            mosaigo <span class="desc">Engine · topics · last-value · Studio · hot-swap · config</span>
          </div>
        </div>
      </section>

      <section class="section">
        <div class="section-label">Roadmap</div>
        <h2>From hand-authored model to live, drift-aware architecture</h2>
        <div class="principle-grid">
          <div class="principle"><div class="principle-num">01</div><div><h4>Hand-authored system + three views + SVG</h4><p>Markdown architecture model. Extract to graph. Developer view, ops view, security view as queries. Render each as SVG.</p></div></div>
          <div class="principle"><div class="principle-num">02</div><div><h4>Ingestion from a real cluster</h4><p>Connect to live k8s. Ingest services, pods, namespaces. Reconcile with hand-authored model.</p></div></div>
          <div class="principle"><div class="principle-num">03</div><div><h4>Terraform + OpenAPI ingestion</h4><p>Terraform state as infrastructure facts. OpenAPI specs as interface definitions. Full deployment pipeline visible.</p></div></div>
          <div class="principle"><div class="principle-num">04</div><div><h4>Interactive viewer</h4><p>Click to drill into a component. See its dependencies, its decisions, its provenance chain.</p></div></div>
          <div class="principle"><div class="principle-num">05</div><div><h4>Options + tradeoff matrices</h4><p>ADRs with options as graph structure. Analyze tradeoffs (cost/performance/security/latency). Visualize decision space.</p></div></div>
          <div class="principle"><div class="principle-num">06</div><div><h4>Capability + business layer</h4><p>Top-down TOGAF: business capabilities → applications → infrastructure. Map decisions to business outcomes.</p></div></div>
          <div class="principle"><div class="principle-num">07</div><div><h4>Info security + data flow</h4><p>Security properties on every node. Data classification flows. Compliance gates as queries ("which components process PII?").</p></div></div>
        </div>
      </section>

      <footer class="footer">
        <div class="footer-links">
          <a href="/staging/">mosaigo</a>
          <a href="/ideas/depict/">depict</a>
          <a href="/ideas/gtmd/">gtmd</a>
          <a href="/ideas/storyarc/">storyarc</a>
          <a href="/ideas/mostrade/">mostrade</a>
          <a href="/ideas/aoc/">aoc</a>
        </div>
        <p>Part of the <a href="/staging/">mosaigoio</a> family · 🧊 draft subproject</p>
      </footer>
    </div>
  </body>
</html>
